1. Uncompress the SGP4 library to main satowl root directory:

satowl
|
+---satowl
|   |
|   ...
|
+---sgp4
|   |
|   ...
|
+---simplefw
|   |
|   +---simplefw.ino
|
+---README
|
...

The library is available at: https://www.danrw.com/sgp4/

2. Install libboost-dev and libserial-dev dependencies on Debian or Ubuntu, or how you would install them on your OS.

3. Go to "satowl" subdirectory and run make there to build the computer side program.

4. Then compile and upload the arduino firmware at "simplefw" directory using Arduino IDE.
